README for libprocess

Most importantly, if you run into an issue, please send me an email:
benh@berkeley.edu.

Instructions:

(1) Configure (in a seperate build directory if you prefer).

path/to/configure

(2) Build.

make

(3) Optional: Build some examples.

cd examples && make

(4) Optional: Build the Python library (assuming you have the Python
headers installed in /usr/include/python2.5, otherwise you can update
swig/Makefile).

cd swig && make python


